sql:
SELECT AVG(sale_price) AS average_sale_price
FROM properties
WHERE neighborhood = 'CollgCr';

external_knowledge:
- 'excellent condition' is inferred to mean an overall condition rating of 6 or higher;
- 'neighborhood's average' refers to the average sale price within the same neighborhood;
- 'start of the new millennium' refers to the year 2000 and beyond.

- 'digital wanderers' refers to the users who access property data;
- 'electronic gates' are the devices used by users to access property data;
- 'explored through more than three electronic gates' means accessing property data using more than three distinct devices.

- 'Sailed the vast ocean of views' refers to accessing property data through 'view' actions; 
- 'More than five times' indicates the condition `COUNT(*) > 5`; 
- 'In the last year' refers to the time range between now and one year ago.

sql:
SELECT sale_date, sale_price
FROM properties
WHERE sale_price = (SELECT MAX(sale_price) FROM properties);
